# E2E Testing (Playwright)

## Auth Helpers
```typescript
import { loginAsRIA } from '../helpers/auth';      // RIA dashboard
import { loginAsClient } from '../helpers/auth';    // Client portal
import { navigateAndVerify } from '../helpers/navigation';
```

## Selector Rules
- Use `getByRole('tab', { name: /.../ })` for tab elements, NOT `getByRole('button')`
- Use `getByRole('button', { name: /.../ })` with specific names to avoid strict violations
- When text matches multiple elements, use `.first()` or narrow with role
- Prefer `aria-label` selectors for icon buttons: `page.locator('button[aria-label="Send message"]')`

## Strict Mode
Playwright strict mode fails when a locator matches multiple elements:
```typescript
// BAD — matches button text AND toast text
await expect(page.getByText(/copied/i)).toBeVisible();

// GOOD — scoped to specific role
await expect(page.getByRole('button', { name: /copied/i })).toBeVisible();
```

## API Mocking
Tests mock API responses via route interception in `e2e/fixtures/` or inline:
```typescript
await page.route('**/api/v1/prospects', route =>
  route.fulfill({ json: mockProspects })
);
```

## Config
- Base URL: `http://localhost:5173` (Vite dev server, auto-started by Playwright)
- `webServer.reuseExistingServer: true` — won't restart if already running
- Retries: 2, timeout: 10s per action
